<div class="row">
  <div class="columns small-12" id="index_bg_container">
    <div class="background-gradient-overlay"></div>
    <!-- this is the orange overlay that is absolute so that it doesnt make everything opaque -->
    <!-- <span class="orange_overlay"></span> -->
    <div class="heading-box">
      <!-- hidden class for search purposes -->
        <h1 class="hidden_h1">Hire.Me</h1>
          <span class="large_headline_first orange-paragraph">hire.</span>
          <span class="large_headline_second">me</span>
        <p class="orange-paragraph">helping working students succeed</p>
        <ul class="menu index-menu">
          <li>
              <%= button_to("Sign Up", access_signup_choice_path, :method => 'get', :class=>"button button-red-large button_spacing") %>
          </li>
          <li>
              <%= link_to("Login", "access/login") %>
          </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="index-search-bar">
    <ul class="menu search-menu">
      <li>
        <%= button_to("search", "", :class=>"button button_spacing search-button") %>
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= text_field_tag "placeholder", nil, :class=>"search-field" %>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row index-content-row">
  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12 picture-index-row">
    <div class="row column spacer">
    </div>

    <div class="row column" id="picture-index-row-1">
      <div class="gradient-overlay gradient-overlay-index"></div>
      <div class="triangle-orange">
        <%= image_tag("triangles.svg", :class => "triangle") %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer spacer-orange">
    </div>

    <div class="row column index-content">
      <h2>What?</h2>
      <p class="larger-body-font">HireMe.com is a website dedicated to helping working students succeed in balancing both school, and having to work
      at the same time. HireMe does this by using innovative job searching techniques, skills based user profiles, quality
      information specifically targeted at working students, and by keeping it free for all.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row index-content-row">
  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer spacer-white">
    </div>

    <div class="row column index-content white-block">
      <h2>Why?</h2>
      <p>Being a working student for my entire student career I realized that it was very difficult to find good paying
      jobs that worked around the schedule that I needed. I chanced upon an opportunity at a local Motorcycle Repair shop
      which was able to give me decent pay with flexible hours thanks to the owners understanding my plight. Unfortunately, even
      taking the maximum hours that they could give me I still needed to pick up a second job. I ended up with the classic
      college student troupe of a delivery driver, but while trying to search for jobs I kept thinking that there had to be
      a better way for a student to search and find work that jibed with a students ever changing schedule.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer">
    </div>

    <div class="row column picture-index-row" id="picture-index-row-2">
      <div class="gradient-overlay gradient-overlay-index"></div>
      <div class="triangle-white">
        <%= image_tag("triangles-white.svg", :class => "triangle") %>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="row index-content-row">
  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12 picture-index-row">
    <div class="row column spacer spacer-white">
    </div>

    <div class="row column" id="picture-index-row-3">
      <div class="gradient-overlay gradient-overlay-index"></div>
      <div class="triangle-orange">
        <%= image_tag("triangles.svg", :class => "triangle") %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer spacer-orange">
    </div>

    <div class="row column index-content">
      <h2>Better Searching</h2>
      <p class="larger-body-font">By providing better tools specifically trageted at the needs of working students. This includes
        better job searching to quickly filter out jobs that have no chance of working with their current, or upcoming,
        school schedule.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row index-content-row">
  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer spacer-white">
    </div>

    <div class="row column index-content white-block">
      <h2>Better Profiles</h2>
      <p class="larger-body-font">User Profiles that work to help showcase the students talent to potential employers instead of only their work
        experience. This includes building a resume like profile that allows students to better describe their skills
        and achievements, showcasing them to potential employers</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="columns medium-6 small-12">
    <div class="row column spacer">
    </div>

